               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office prayers and litanies (fols. 4ra-11vb)
 II) Śǝrʿāta
                     qǝddāse "Ordinary of the Mass" (fols. 12ra-44vb)
 III) Anaphoras (fols.
                     45ra-131rb)
 III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 45ra-58rb)
 III-2)
                     Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 59ra-62rb), preceded by "The Covenant
                     of the Lord" (fols. 58va-59ra)
 III-3) Anaphora of St John, son of Thunder
                     (fols. 62rb-70rb)
 III-4) Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa
                     (fols. 70ra-79ra)
 III-5) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea
                     (fols. 79ra-86rb)
 III-6) Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols.
                     86va-95vb)
 III-7) Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea (fols. 95vb-102vb)
                     III-8) Anaphora of St Gregory of Armenia ("Hosanna-liturgy of St Gregory")
                     (fols. 102vb-107va)
 III-9) Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus (fols.
                     107va-112rb)
 III-10) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom (fols.
                     112rb-116va)
 III-11) Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols.
                     116va-121rb)
 III-12) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols.
                     121rb-126rb)
 III-13) Anaphora of St Dioscorus of Alexandria
                     (fols.126va-128va)
 III-14) Second Anaphora of St Gregory
                     ("Christmas-liturgy of St Gregory")(fols. 128va-131rb)
 
 Additiones
                     1-2.</summary>
